# After the first Zenodo release, paste the concept DOI into `identifiers` and `doi` below.
cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this artifact, please cite it as below."
title: >-
  PG-Agent & ERP-AuthZBench: Authorization-Preserving LLM Agents over ERP,
  with a Policy-Closure Compiler
abstract: >-
  A model-agnostic, data-result-plane Policy Enforcement Point (PEP) for ERP LLM agents on Odoo, the
  ERP-AuthZBench adversarial benchmark for row-level authorization, and PCC-ERP, a policy-closure compiler that
  derives, emits, and runtime-verifies per-model row closures from the ORM relation graph. Includes a one-command,
  byte-diff reproducible artifact-evaluation harness.
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Truong
    given-names: Vinh Khuong
repository-code: "https://github.com/truongvinhkhuong/pg-agent"
license: MIT
version: "1.0.0"
# date-released: update to the actual Zenodo release date, e.g. 2026-07-01
keywords:
  - LLM agents
  - ERP security
  - row-level authorization
  - policy enforcement point
  - confused deputy
  - relational-traversal
  - Odoo
  - policy-closure compiler
